1. Pesticides – Classification and Effects
Pesticides are chemical or biological agents used to kill, repel, or control pests (insects, weeds, fungi, rodents,
nematodes). While essential for agriculture, they pose serious environmental and health risks through
persistence, bioaccumulation, and non-target organism toxicity.
